            <!-- ═══ SECTION 4: CONTENT FRAMEWORK ═══ -->
            <section id="framework">
                <div class="section-label">Section 04</div>
                <h2 contenteditable="true">Content Framework</h2>
                <p class="section-intro" contenteditable="true">Two complementary frameworks for presenting Engagement — one journey-based for the page narrative, one persona-based for use case positioning.</p>

                <h3>Framework A — The Engagement Journey</h3>
                <p contenteditable="true">This is the primary organizing principle for the /engagement page. It presents the module as a continuous loop, not a feature list. Each stage maps to specific product capabilities and business outcomes.</p>

                <div class="journey-flow">
                    <div class="journey-step">
                        <div class="step-icon">👟</div>
                        <div class="step-title" contenteditable="true">Track</div>
                        <div class="step-desc" contenteditable="true">Step sync from wearables & phones. Daily activity dashboards. Streaks that build habits over weeks, not days.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="journey-step">
                        <div class="step-icon">⚔️</div>
                        <div class="step-title" contenteditable="true">Compete</div>
                        <div class="step-desc" contenteditable="true">Peer challenges with invites. CUG-wide campaigns. Steps Premier League — team battles with leaderboards and match commentary.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="journey-step">
                        <div class="step-icon">📚</div>
                        <div class="step-title" contenteditable="true">Learn</div>
                        <div class="step-desc" contenteditable="true">Live webinars with Q&A. Expert articles. On-demand wellness videos. Knowledge that reinforces healthy behaviors.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="journey-step">
                        <div class="step-icon">🎁</div>
                        <div class="step-title" contenteditable="true">Earn</div>
                        <div class="step-desc" contenteditable="true">Milestone rewards. Challenge prizes. Voucher economy with real-world redemption. Habit Coins that make engagement tangible.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="callout insight">
                    <div class="callout-title">Why This Framework Works</div>
                    <p contenteditable="true">It answers the buyer's implicit question: "What does the employee experience actually look like?" By walking through Track → Compete → Learn → Earn, you show a complete engagement ecosystem — not disconnected features. It also mirrors the actual behavior change model: build awareness (Track), create motivation (Compete), provide knowledge (Learn), reinforce with incentives (Earn).</p>
                </div>

                <h3>Framework B — Use Case Positioning</h3>
                <p contenteditable="true">For buyers who think in terms of "who uses this and how?" — present three clear use case lanes.</p>

                <div class="card-grid-3">
                    <div class="use-case hr">
                        <div class="uc-label">HR-Driven</div>
                        <div class="uc-title" contenteditable="true">Campaign Management</div>
                        <p contenteditable="true" style="font-size:13.5px;">HR admins design, launch, and track organization-wide wellness campaigns from a central dashboard.</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li contenteditable="true">CUG challenges with custom goals & durations</li>
                            <li contenteditable="true">SPL league setup with team allocation</li>
                            <li contenteditable="true">Content scheduling (webinars, articles, VOD)</li>
                            <li contenteditable="true">Reward configuration & budget controls</li>
                            <li contenteditable="true">Real-time participation analytics</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="use-case employee">
                        <div class="uc-label">Employee-Driven</div>
                        <div class="uc-title" contenteditable="true">Social Wellness</div>
                        <p contenteditable="true" style="font-size:13.5px;">Employees create their own challenges, invite peers, and build healthy habits through social accountability.</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li contenteditable="true">Create personal step challenges</li>
                            <li contenteditable="true">Invite colleagues to compete</li>
                            <li contenteditable="true">Track daily streaks & milestones</li>
                            <li contenteditable="true">Browse and join open challenges</li>
                            <li contenteditable="true">Earn rewards through consistent participation</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="use-case org">
                        <div class="uc-label">Organization-Wide</div>
                        <div class="uc-title" contenteditable="true">Culture Events</div>
                        <p contenteditable="true" style="font-size:13.5px;">Large-scale engagement events that unite entire campuses or business units around shared health goals.</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li contenteditable="true">Steps Premier League (cross-team competition)</li>
                            <li contenteditable="true">Multi-campus challenges with local leaderboards</li>
                            <li contenteditable="true">Sports facility booking for campus events</li>
                            <li contenteditable="true">Live wellness webinars at scale</li>
                            <li contenteditable="true">Organization-wide rewards & recognition</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h3>Content Flow — How the Page Should Read</h3>
                <div class="card">
                    <p contenteditable="true" style="margin-bottom:0;">The page narrative should follow this arc: <strong>Hook</strong> (outcome headline — answer "why should I care?") → <strong>System</strong> (Track → Compete → Learn → Earn journey — show the full engagement loop) → <strong>Depth</strong> (feature deep-dives with product visuals — answer "how does it work?") → <strong>Proof</strong> (metrics, testimonials, case study — answer "does it actually work?") → <strong>Relevance</strong> (use case lanes or role-based view — answer "how does it apply to my org?") → <strong>Action</strong> (demo CTA — make the next step obvious).</p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <div class="page-break"></div>

            <!-- ═══ SECTION 5: DIFFERENTIATION ═══ -->
            <section id="differentiation">
                <div class="section-label">Section 05</div>
                <h2 contenteditable="true">Differentiation Strategy</h2>
                <p class="section-intro" contenteditable="true">What makes Habit Health's Engagement genuinely different from Wellable, Virgin Pulse, YuMuuv, and Vantage Fit — and how to communicate it.</p>

                <h3>Unique Differentiators to Highlight</h3>
                <p contenteditable="true">These features are genuinely uncommon or absent in competitor platforms. They should be named, explained, and positioned prominently — not hidden in app screenshots.</p>

                <div class="card-grid">
                    <div class="accent-card primary">
                        <h4>Steps Premier League (SPL)</h4>
                        <p contenteditable="true">An IPL-style corporate step competition with teams, captains, match days, cricket-themed scoring (Sixers, Boundaries, Outs), and live commentary. No major competitor offers anything like this — it turns step tracking into a spectator sport within the organization. <strong>This is the single most differentiating feature and deserves hero-level treatment.</strong></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accent-card secondary">
                        <h4>Employee-Created Peer Challenges</h4>
                        <p contenteditable="true">Employees can create their own step challenges, set goals, invite specific colleagues, and compete on personal leaderboards. Most competitors offer only admin-led challenges. This bottom-up engagement model creates organic virality and reduces HR overhead.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accent-card amber">
                        <h4>CUG-Based Multi-Tenant Architecture</h4>
                        <p contenteditable="true">Challenges, content, events, and rewards can be configured per Closed User Group — supporting multi-campus, multi-BU, and multi-client deployments from a single platform. Most competitors require separate instances for different organizational units. For large enterprises, this is a procurement advantage.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accent-card violet">
                        <h4>Integrated Engagement Ecosystem</h4>
                        <p contenteditable="true">Tracking, challenges, content, webinars, facility bookings, and rewards all live in one platform — not stitched together from acquisitions or integrations. The engagement loop (Track → Compete → Learn → Earn) is native, not assembled. This means faster setup, consistent UX, and unified analytics.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

