            <!-- ═══ SECTION 6: VISUAL & UX ═══ -->
            <section id="visuals">
                <div class="section-label">Section 06</div>
                <h2 contenteditable="true">Visual & UX Recommendations</h2>
                <p class="section-intro" contenteditable="true">What to show, how to show it, and what types of visual content will make Engagement tangible for buyers who can't do a live demo yet.</p>

                <div class="visual-rec">
                    <div class="v-icon" style="background:rgba(15,76,129,0.08);">📱</div>
                    <div class="v-content">
                        <div class="v-title" contenteditable="true">Full-Screen Product Screenshots (Not Thumbnails)</div>
                        <div class="v-desc" contenteditable="true">Replace the current tiny carousel mockups with large, legible app screenshots. Each feature section should have a hero-sized product visual that a buyer can understand without zooming. Show the SPL leaderboard, a live challenge with progress bars, the streak calendar, and the rewards screen at a size where the data is readable.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="visual-rec">
                    <div class="v-icon" style="background:rgba(0,168,120,0.08);">🎬</div>
                    <div class="v-content">
                        <div class="v-title" contenteditable="true">60-Second Engagement Product Video</div>
                        <div class="v-desc" contenteditable="true">Create a short, narrated screen recording that walks through the engagement journey: opening the app, seeing the step dashboard, joining a challenge, checking the leaderboard, winning a reward. This single asset has more conversion power than 2,000 words of copy. Place it in the hero section with a "Watch How It Works" CTA. Auto-muted, with captions.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="visual-rec">
                    <div class="v-icon" style="background:rgba(108,92,231,0.08);">📊</div>
                    <div class="v-content">
                        <div class="v-title" contenteditable="true">Admin Dashboard Preview</div>
                        <div class="v-desc" contenteditable="true">HR buyers need to see the administrative experience — not just the employee app. Show a screenshot or animated mockup of the admin dashboard: creating a challenge, viewing participation analytics, managing reward budgets. This addresses the unspoken buyer question: "Will this create more work for my team?"</div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="visual-rec">
                    <div class="v-icon" style="background:rgba(232,145,58,0.08);">🔄</div>
                    <div class="v-content">
                        <div class="v-title" contenteditable="true">Animated Engagement Journey Flow</div>
                        <div class="v-desc" contenteditable="true">The Track → Compete → Learn → Earn framework should be visualized as an animated loop or interactive scroll-triggered diagram. As the user scrolls, each stage lights up with product screenshots and key stats. This replaces the static feature cards with something that communicates "system" rather than "list."</div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="visual-rec">
                    <div class="v-icon" style="background:rgba(217,79,107,0.08);">📈</div>
                    <div class="v-content">
                        <div class="v-title" contenteditable="true">Outcome Metrics — Large Format</div>
                        <div class="v-desc" contenteditable="true">Display engagement outcomes as large, bold stat blocks — e.g., "8,000+ SPL Participants", "3× Engagement vs. Industry Average", "85% Challenge Completion Rate." Use real numbers from HCLT deployments where available. These should be visually prominent (large font, colored backgrounds) and placed near the top of the page, not buried at the bottom.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="visual-rec">
                    <div class="v-icon" style="background:rgba(15,76,129,0.08);">💬</div>
                    <div class="v-content">
                        <div class="v-title" contenteditable="true">Engagement-Specific Testimonials</div>
                        <div class="v-desc" contenteditable="true">The current testimonials section has zero mentions of engagement. Source 2–3 quotes specifically about challenges, SPL, or participation outcomes. Even internal quotes from HCLT HR leadership or pilot champions count. Place them adjacent to feature sections — a testimonial about SPL next to the SPL feature description, not in a generic carousel at the bottom.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="callout action">
                    <div class="callout-title">UX Principle</div>
                    <p contenteditable="true">The page should be scannable in 15 seconds and readable in 2 minutes. A buyer should be able to scroll through and understand what Engagement does, how it's different, and whether it's credible — without reading a single paragraph. Visuals, stats, and feature names do the heavy lifting. Body copy provides depth for those who want it.</p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <div class="page-break"></div>

            <!-- ═══ SECTION 7: IMPLEMENTATION ═══ -->
            <section id="implementation">
                <div class="section-label">Section 07</div>
                <h2 contenteditable="true">Quick Wins vs Strategic Changes</h2>
                <p class="section-intro" contenteditable="true">A prioritized implementation plan separated by effort level, so the team can ship immediate improvements while planning the larger overhaul.</p>

                <h3>Quick Wins — Can Ship This Week</h3>
                <p contenteditable="true">These require no new pages, no design work, and no content creation. They're copy changes and reordering.</p>

                <div class="impl-item">
                    <span class="impl-effort quick">Quick Win</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Fix the broken "Our Solutions" page</strong>
                        <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);margin:4px 0 0;">The primary buyer discovery path is completely dead. This is a technical bug with high credibility impact — fix it before anything else.</p>
                    </div>
                    <span class="tag tag-critical">Critical</span>
                </div>

                <div class="impl-item">
                    <span class="impl-effort quick">Quick Win</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Change the homepage carousel default to Engagement</strong>
                        <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);margin:4px 0 0;">Set the app carousel's default slide to the Steps Premier League or Active Zone screen. Currently defaults to "Employee Health Benefits" and "Tele Consultation."</p>
                    </div>
                    <span class="tag tag-quick">1 Hour</span>
                </div>

                <div class="impl-item">
                    <span class="impl-effort quick">Quick Win</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Rewrite the "Engagement engine" card on Habit Health page</strong>
                        <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);margin:4px 0 0;">Replace "Gamification, nudges, and social features boost participation" (12 words) with outcome-driven copy: "Challenges, leagues, streaks, and rewards that drive 70%+ sustained participation — turning wellness programs into organizational movements."</p>
                    </div>
                    <span class="tag tag-quick">30 Min</span>
                </div>

                <div class="impl-item">
                    <span class="impl-effort quick">Quick Win</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Move "Gamified wellness" section to top of Wellness Offerings page</strong>
                        <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);margin:4px 0 0;">Currently the last section. Move it to position 1 or 2 — above Clinical Support and Knowledge Sessions. The information hierarchy should signal priority.</p>
                    </div>
                    <span class="tag tag-quick">30 Min</span>
                </div>

                <div class="impl-item">
                    <span class="impl-effort quick">Quick Win</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Add feature names to app screenshot captions</strong>
                        <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);margin:4px 0 0;">Where app mockups show SPL, challenges, or rewards — add visible text labels below: "Steps Premier League — team-based corporate step competition" instead of relying on the buyer to read tiny in-app text.</p>
                    </div>
                    <span class="tag tag-quick">1 Hour</span>
                </div>

                <h3>Medium-Term — 2 to 4 Weeks</h3>

                <div class="impl-item">
                    <span class="impl-effort medium">Medium</span>
